OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1777554668
OL,3,CDrivers warned to be vigilant on roads
OL,4,Cas likelihood of hitting deer rises
OL,6,FThe number of deer being killed on our
OL,7,Froads has risen and the risk of
OL,8,Faccidents is set to soar in May.
OL,10,FThe AA, based in Basingstoke, is
OL,11,Fwarning all drivers to be vigilant.
OL,13,FThey say, on average, 90 members are
OL,14,Fhelped a month due to deer strikes,
OL,15,Fbut this increases by as much as 50%
OL,16,Fin May when compared to other months.
OL,18,FOne young driver says his insurance is
OL,19,Fnow going up as a result of him
OL,20,Fhitting a deer which jumped out in
OL,21,Ffront of him without warning.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
